import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['time'])]
    
    plt.plot(data['time'], data['count'])
    plt.xlabel('Time')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the overall trend of count over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Count'])
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['time'])]
    
    plt.hist(data['count'], bins='auto', color='blue', alpha=0.7, rwidth=0.85)
    plt.axvline(data['count'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['count'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Count')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of count?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['time'])]
    data['day'] = data['time'].dt.date
    daily_average = data.groupby('day')['count'].mean().reset_index()

    plt.bar(daily_average['day'], daily_average['count'])
    plt.xlabel('Day')
    plt.ylabel('Average Count')
    plt.title('What is the average count per day?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['time'])]
    data['month'] = data['time'].dt.to_period('M')
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    data.boxplot(column='count', by='month', ax=ax)
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of count for each month?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Month')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    plt.suptitle('')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
